Deliver Prescription Drug (Naproxen) - No contest plea.  Convicted.   Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Four (4) months jail; Two (2) months, up front, under the Huber Law, to commence on 11-03-15 at 8:00 a.m.   Two (2) months, stayed to be imposed upon the agent's discretion;
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5) Maintain full-time employment/school combination;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Submit DNA sample and pay the surcharge; 
Court finds that defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment of record pursuant to Section 973.015 of the Wisconsin Statutes upon successful completion of sentence.  
